Operation Dudula. JOHANNESBURG - Operation Dudula is heading back to Hillbrow. Organisers of the controversial group claim they're removing undocumented foreign traders and drug dealers. Police blocked the campaign last week using water cannons and rubber bullets. READ: Makhura wants to work with Operation Dudula Officials said the required permission and permits were not granted. Now, Dudula organisers say they will return to finish their work. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala shares more details in the videos below. eNCA's Nqobile Madlalla has the latest on this story. Courtesy #DStv403 A strong police presence in Hillbrow in Johannesburg where some members of civic group Operation Dudula are gathering for a march against illegal foreigners. Courtesy #DStv403